  <prompt>
    Author `ListSessionFilesHandler` (NEW) at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/ListSessionFilesHandler.cs` implementing the T2 `list_session_files` tool per architecture §8.1. The handler reads `ChatSession.UploadedFiles` (extended in task 071) and returns the enriched per-file array (fileId, fileName, contentType, sizeBytes, pageCount?, uploadedAt, uploadedBy, classifiedDocType, classifiedConfidence, precomputedSummary marked NOT authoritative in description, sections, recentlyDiscussed, citationsReferenced). Implements FR-30 (list_session_files row of the 8-tool surface).
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in chat tool-handler authoring + auto-discovered `sprk_analysistool` registration.</role>

  <goal>
    `ListSessionFilesHandler` lives at `Services/Ai/Handlers/ListSessionFilesHandler.cs` implementing `IToolHandler`. Returns single `ToolResult` (no streaming, per ADR-033). Auto-discovered via `AddToolHandlersFromAssembly`. The handler reads through `IChatSessionManager` (or equivalent persistence accessor) to fetch the current session's `UploadedFiles`. Tool description embeds the architecture §2 P3 trust framing — the `precomputedSummary` field is marked "NOT authoritative; call `recall_session_file(requireCitations:true)` for legally-precise answers". Unit tests cover: zero files, multiple files, recentlyDiscussed flag flips, citationsReferenced shape. Telemetry emits handler name + sessionId + file count + duration ONLY (ADR-015 tier-1 safe).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §3.1 (Tier 2 Session memory) + §4.2 dependency graph + §8.1 Tool Surface + §8.2 (Tool routing — list_session_files reads T2, no writes, always-on when session has files). The handler wraps existing `ChatSession.UploadedFiles[]` access. Architecture §4.4 catalogs this as one of the 8 NEW tool handlers. FR-30 in spec.md lists it as part of the tool surface expansion.
    </background>
